__NAME__ purpose
send raw-formatted e-mail using SendMailProgram
__END__


__NAME__ synopsis
&TAG_CONTAINER;
__END__


__NAME__ see also
email, SendMailProgram, customsendmail
__END__


__NAME__ description
This tag simply feeds <option>SendMailProgram</option> with the raw-formatted
e-mail body that you provide.
</para><para>
This means you also need to provide all the headers yourself.
Header lines must be at the beginning of the line, and the header
must have a valid <literal>To:</literal> field, or the message surely
won't be delivered.
__END__


__NAME__ example: Simple raw e-mail message
Put the following on a test page:
<programlisting>
[email-raw]
From: test@localhost
To: root@localhost
Subject: DEAR FRIEND

THROUGH THE COURTESY OF BUSINESS OPPORTUNITY, I TAKE LIBERTY ANCHORED ON A
STRONG DESIRE TO SOLICIT YOUR ASSISTANCE ON THIS MUTUALLY BENEFICIAL AND
RISKFREE TRANSACTION WHICH I HOPE YOU WILL GIVE YOUR URGENT ATTENTION.

I HAVE DEPOSITED THE SUM OF THIRTY MILLION,FIVE HUNDRED THOUSAND UNITED
STATES DOLLARS(US$30,500,000) WITH A SECURITY COMPANY FOR SAFEKEEPING.
THE FUNDS ARE SECURITY CODED TO PREVENT THEM FROM KNOWING THE ACTUAL
CONTENTS.

MAY I AT THIS POINT EMPHASIZE THE HIGH LEVEL OF CONFIDENTIALLITY WHICH THIS
BUSINESS DEMANDS AND HOPE YOU WILL NOT BETRAY THE TRUST AND CONFIDENCE WHICH
WE REPOSE IN YOU.
[/email-raw]
</programlisting>
We hope you will recognize an attempt at humor in the example above, and
won't use it as an idea for
<ulink url="http://spam.abuse.net/">spamming</ulink> activities.
__END__

